          {# <h2 id="about-the-scheme">About the scheme</h2> #}

<p>
  The <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/animal-health-and-welfare-pathway/animal-health-and-welfare-pathway">Animal Health and Welfare Pathway</a> supports continuous improvement in farm animal health and welfare.
</p>

<p>The following is all the funding currently available through the Pathway.</p>

<div class="example">
  {# <p>Example</p>

  <p>If an employee works 3 days a week, one ‘week’ of parental leave equals 3 days. If an employee works irregular weeks the number of days in a ‘week’ is the total number of days they work a year divided by 52.</p> #}
  <p>This page will be updated whenever a new scheme opens or an existing scheme closes.</p>
</div>


<h2 id="iahw">Animal Health and Welfare Review (AHWR) for cattle, pigs and sheep</h2>

<p>Funding is available for an annual vet visit to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>assess the health and welfare of animals on your farm</li>
  <li>help you plan improvements</li>
</ul>

<p>Reviews include tailored advice from a vet and testing for priority endemic diseases.</p>

<p>The amount of funding depends on the species you keep.</p>

{# <h3>Find out more about AHWR</h3> #}

{# <ul style="list-style-type: none; margin-left: 0;">
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/farmers-how-to-apply-for-funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare">Apply for funding to improve animal health and welfare</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare-guidance-for-farmers-and-vets">Funding to improve cattle, pig and sheep health and welfare: guidance for farmers and vets</a></li>
</ul> #}

<p>Read <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/farmers-how-to-apply-for-funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare">IAHW guidance for farmers and vets</a>.</p>
 {# or <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare-guidance-for-farmers-and-vets">apply for funding</a> #}
 {# .</p> #}
{# <ul style="list-style-type: none; margin-left: 0;">
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/farmers-how-to-apply-for-funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare">Apply for funding to improve animal health and welfare</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare-guidance-for-farmers-and-vets">Funding to improve cattle, pig and sheep health and welfare: guidance for farmers and vets</a></li>
</ul> #}

<h2 id="edf">Endemic Disease Follow-up (EDF)</h2>

<p>Funding is available for:</p>

<ul>
  <li>follow-up testing</li>
  <li>diagnostics</li>
  <li>advisory visits after an AHWR</li>
</ul>

<p>The follow-up helps you address priority endemic diseases and improve long-term herd and flock health.</p>

<p>You can claim for an EDF after completing an AHWR.</p>

{# <h3>Find out more about AHWR</h3> #}

{# <ul style="list-style-type: none; margin-left: 0;">
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/farmers-how-to-apply-for-funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare">Apply for funding to improve animal health and welfare</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare-guidance-for-farmers-and-vets">Funding to improve cattle, pig and sheep health and welfare: guidance for farmers and vets</a></li>
</ul> #}

<p>Read <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/farmers-how-to-apply-for-funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare">EDF guidance for farmers and vets</a>.</p>
 {# or <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare-guidance-for-farmers-and-vets">apply for funding</a> #}
 {# .</p> #}


<h2 id="pbr">Poultry Biosecurity Review</h2>

<p>Funding is available to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>support commercial poultry keepers to strengthen biosecurity</li>
  <li>reduce disease risks</li>
</ul>

<p>The review includes an on-site assessment by a vet or vet team with tailored recommendations to improve biosecurity practices.</p>

{# <h3>Find out more about Poultry Biosecurity Reviews</h3> #}

{# <ul style="list-style-type: none; margin-left: 0;">
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/farmers-how-to-apply-for-funding-to-improve-animal-health-and-welfare">Apply for funding to improve animal health and welfare</a></li>
  <li><a href="index">Poultry Biosecurity Review funding: guidance for poultry keepers and vets</a></li>
</ul> #}

<p>Read <a href="index">Poultry Biosecurity Review guidance for poultry keepers and vets</a>.</p>
 {# or <a href="../new-user/sign-in-crn?poultry=no&cattle=no&populated=false">apply for funding</a> #}
 {# .</p> #}

<h2 id="fetf">Farming Equipment and Technology Fund (FETF)</h2>

<p>Grants are available for equipment and technology that helps you boost the health and welfare outcomes for your herd or flock. This includes:</p>

<ul>
  <li>handling</li>
  <li>monitoring</li>
  <li>enrichment</li>
  <li>disease prevention</li>
  <li>housing</li>
</ul>

<p>Applications for the grant are competitive. The application window for this year closes at 12:00pm on 28 April 2026.</p>

{# <h3>Find out more about FETF</h3> #}

{# <ul style="list-style-type: none; margin-left: 0;">
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/farming-equipment-and-technology-fund-fetf-2026/animal-health-and-welfare-items-and-specifications-farming-equipment-and-technology-fund-fetf-2026">FETF 2026: Animal health and welfare items and specifications</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/farming-equipment-and-technology-fund-fetf-2026">FETF 2026 – overview and how to apply</a></li>
</ul> #}

<p>Read <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/farming-equipment-and-technology-fund-fetf-2026/animal-health-and-welfare-items-and-specifications-farming-equipment-and-technology-fund-fetf-2026">FETF guidance for farmers and vets</a>.</p>
{# or <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/farming-equipment-and-technology-fund-fetf-2026">apply for funding</a> #}


